olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet dried oregano
½ cucumber
2 clove garlic
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ packet Cow's Milk Feta
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over 1/2 the dried oregano, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, grate cucumber (see ingredients) and squeeze out any excess moisture using a paper towel or clean cloth. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl, then add Greek-style yoghurt and cucumber and stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

• Drain liquid from beef strip packaging.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef, garlic & herb seasoning, remaining dried oregano, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then add the honey and toss to coat.

• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.
• In a second medium bowl, combine baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Top tortillas with tzatziki, dressed baby spinach, beef strips and some oregano fries. Crumble over feta (see ingredients).
• Serve with any remaining fries and tzatziki. Enjoy!